Description: GOcontext provides tools for constructing context-specific
    subgraphs of the Gene Ontology (GO) to restrict the hypothesis
    space prior to functional enrichment analysis. The package enables
    curated or keyword-derived GO seed selection, graph-based expansion
    within a GO DAG, optional semantic similarity refinement using
    GOSemSim, and formal subgraph restriction. Resulting subgraphs can
    be used to filter TERM2GENE mappings, gene set collections, or
    annotation tables before statistical testing. This approach reduces
    multiple testing burden in a principled manner while preserving
    ontology structure and reproducibility.
